text: Abulfaz Elchibey, ( / Әбүлфәз Елчибәј; 24 June 1938 – 22 August 2000) was an Azerbaijani politician. He became leader of the Azerbaijani Popular Front in 1990. Elchibey was the second President of Azerbaijan, from 16 June 1992 until a coup d'état took him out of office in June 1993. ==References== Category:1938 births Category:2000 deaths Category:Presidents of Azerbaijan Category:Azerbaijani Popular Front Party politicians Category:Deaths from prostate cancer Category:Cancer deaths in Turkey Category:Azerbaijani historians Category:Azerbaijani writers Category:Azerbaijani nationalists Category:Burials at Alley of Honor Category:Soviet politicians Category:20th- century Azerbaijani people
